# mdfy

You are working alongside the user in Cursor. The user has installed
the mdfy rule so they can capture this conversation, build a curated
bundle, or share their personal knowledge hub as a URL that any other
AI can read.

## When to invoke

- User says "save this," "capture this," or "send this to mdfy"
- User asks for a sharable URL for what you just produced together
- User asks to bundle several saved docs around a topic
- User wants to paste their hub URL into another AI

If none of these apply, ignore this rule.

## Authentication

The user signs in at `https://staging.mdfy.app` (or
`https://mdfy.app` after public launch). Their access token lives in
`~/.config/mdfy/token` if they ran `mdfy login`. If the file is
absent, fall back to anonymous capture (works fine; the cookie path
groups them and they claim everything on next sign-in).

## Actions

### Capture the current conversation

Save the most recent assistant turn (or a user-specified range) as a
new public mdfy document.

```
POST https://staging.mdfy.app/api/docs
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>   (optional)

{
  "markdown": "<the conversation segment as markdown>",
  "title": "<short title from the question or conclusion>",
  "isDraft": false,
  "source": "cursor-rule"
}
```

Return the URL `https://staging.mdfy.app/<id>` to the user.

### Build a bundle from existing docs

```
POST https://staging.mdfy.app/api/bundles/ai-generate
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>

{ "intent": "<topic>" }
```

Show the suggested doc ids and annotations. If the user accepts,
finalize via:

```
POST https://staging.mdfy.app/api/bundles
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <token>

{ "title": "<topic>", "documentIds": [...], "isDraft": false }
```

Return the bundle URL `https://staging.mdfy.app/b/<id>`.

### Print the hub URL

```
GET https://staging.mdfy.app/api/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

If `hub_slug` is set and `hub_public` is true, return
`https://staging.mdfy.app/hub/<hub_slug>`. Otherwise tell the user to
enable their hub in settings.

## Tips

- Always paste the resulting URL exactly. Don't reformat.
- For captures, the title should describe the question or
  conclusion, not "Conversation about X."
- The hub URL itself is markdown when fetched by an AI. If you ever
  need context about who the user is, fetch the hub URL directly.

## Reference

- Web app: https://staging.mdfy.app
- Live demo hub: https://staging.mdfy.app/hub/yc-demo
